
[1]lothsome

   LO'THSOME, a.

   1. Causing an extreme aversion of appetite; exciting fastidiousness.
   Num. 11.

   2. Exciting extreme disgust; offensive; as a lothsome disease. Ps. 38.

   3. Odious; exciting hatred or abhorrence; detestable; as lothsome
   sloth.
